    "The index i 0 runs over all neurons which fire a spike.",
    "For these neurons we add the transmission cost to the charging energy, calculated simply using the threshold value ϑ ðnÞ i 0.",
    "Analogously, for all neurons that do not spike (index i 00) the charging energy is calculated using the value of the potential V ðnÞ i 00 at time instant t ðnÞ max, which is smaller than the threshold ϑ ðnÞ i 00.",
    "Therefore, when a neuron spikes it contributes a larger share to the energy consumption than when it stays silent.",
    "To estimate the average capacitor energy per neuron we use the definition θ 2 = ð1=NÞ P i ðϑ ðnÞ i Þ 2 where the sum runs over all neurons in all layers."
